  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "What are some favorite YouTube Hacks?",
  "response": "YouTube hacks can help improve your viewing experience, enhance productivity, and make content creation easier. Here are some favorite YouTube hacks:\n\n### Viewing Hacks\n1. **Keyboard Shortcuts**: Efficiently navigate YouTube with keyboard shortcuts such as:\n   - `K`: Pause/Play video\n   - `J`: Rewind 10 seconds\n   - `L`: Fast forward 10 seconds\n   - `M`: Mute/Unmute\n   - `F`: Enter/Exit fullscreen\n   - `Arrow Keys`: Navigate through the video\n\n2. **Transcript Search**: Click on the three dots below the video (next to the Share button) and select \"Open transcript\". Use Ctrl+F (Cmd+F on Mac) to search for specific words within the transcript.\n\n3. **Video Quality Settings**: Manually setting video quality to improve or decrease resolution can enhance viewing experience based on your internet speed. Click on the gear icon and choose your desired quality.\n\n4. **URL Tricks**: Use these URL modifications for different needs:\n   - Start video at specific time: Add `?t=1m30s` at the end to start at 1 minute 30 seconds.\n   - Loop video: Type `repeat` between `youtube` and `.com` (e.g., youtube.com becomes youtuberepeat.com).\n\n5. **Speed Controls**: Use the settings (gear icon) to change the playback speed to watch the video faster or slower.\n\n### Content Creation Hacks\n6. **Captions/Subtitles**: Automatically generate captions and then edit them for accuracy. This makes your videos more accessible and can improve SEO.\n\n7. **Using Analytics**: Regularly check YouTube Analytics to understand the performance of your videos, audience demographics, and engagement metrics.\n\n8. **Custom Thumbnails**: Create compelling thumbnails to increase your video\u2019s click-through rate. Use tools like Canva or Adobe Spark for designing good-quality thumbnails.\n\n9. **Optimizing Titles and Descriptions**: Use keywords that are relevant to your content and audience. Research trending topics and incorporate them into your titles and descriptions.\n\n### Productivity Hacks\n10. **Ad Blockers**: Install browser extensions like AdBlock to enjoy uninterrupted viewing.\n\n11. **MiniPlayer**: Use the MiniPlayer mode (bottom right corner when watching a video) to browse YouTube while watching content.\n\n12. **Watch Later Playlist**: Add videos to your \u201cWatch Later\u201d playlist to organize what you want to view in the future.\n\n13. **YouTube Premium**: Consider subscribing to YouTube Premium for ad-free viewing, background play, and access to exclusive content.\n\n### Mobile App Hacks\n14. **Double Tap Gestures**: Double tap on the left or right side of the screen to rewind or fast forward 10 seconds.\n\n15. **Offline Viewing**: Available with YouTube Premium, download videos for offline viewing.\n\n16. **Background Play**: YouTube Premium allows you to play videos in the background while using other apps.\n\n### Bonus Hack\n17. **Channel URL Trick for Subscribers**: Direct visitors to your subscription link by appending `?sub_confirmation=1` to your channel URL (e.g., `youtube.com/yourchannel?sub_confirmation=1`).\n\nThese hacks aim to enhance both your viewing and content creation experience on YouTube.",
